<p style=3D"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:10pt; line-height:115%; font-size=
:10pt"> <br> <span style=3D"font-family:'Amazon Ember'; font-size:9pt">AWS =
will provide a multi-layered approach to Ingress network security utilizing=
 some/all of the following services:</span> <br> <br> <span style=3D"font-f=
amily:'Amazon Ember'; font-size:9pt; font-weight:bold">AWS Shield </span> <=
span style=3D"font-family:'Amazon Ember'; font-size:9pt">is a managed DDos =
Service. AWS Shield Standard defends against most common, frequently occuri=
ng network and transport layer DDoS attacks. It is provided at no extra cha=
rge and does not require any configuration. When used in conjunction with A=
mazon CloudFront a fully managed CDN and Amazon Route 53 a highly available=
 and scalable Domain Name System Shield Standard will protect agains all kn=
own infrastructrure (Layer 3 and 4) attacks.</span> <br> <br> <span style=
=3D"font-family:'Amazon Ember'; font-size:9pt; font-weight:bold">AWS Shield=
 Advanced</span> <span style=3D"font-family:'Amazon Ember'; font-size:9pt">=
 provides additional protections and mitigation agains large and sophiticat=
ed DDoS attacks, near real time visibility into attacks and integration wit=
h AWS, a web application firewall. AWS Shield Advanced provides 24x7 access=
 to the AWS DDoS Response Team (DRT), who can optionally be provided with a=
ccess to provide a managed mitigation service in the event of an attack. AW=
S Shield Advanced will also provide protection against additional charges i=
ncurred during a DDoS attack against your EC2, ELB, Amazon CloudFront, AWS =
Global Accelerator and Amazon Route 53 charges.</span> <br> <br> <span styl=
e=3D"font-family:'Amazon Ember'; font-size:9pt; font-weight:bold">Amazon Cl=
oudFront</span> <span style=3D"font-family:'Amazon Ember'; font-size:9pt"> =
is a highly scaleable, fully managed fast content delivery network (CDN) th=
at will form a layer of protection for backend services from high volume DD=
oS attacks by serving contents directly. It can also be configured to inclu=
de or exclude traffic from certain countries using Geo-Restriction.</span> =
<br> <br> <span style=3D"font-family:'Amazon Ember'; font-size:9pt; font-we=
ight:bold">Amazon Route 53</span> <span style=3D"font-family:'Amazon Ember'=
; font-size:9pt"> is a Domain Name System (DNS) web service. It has a numbe=
r of features that can be used to mitigate DDoS attacks. This includes rout=
ing based on Latency or Geoproximity. Route 53 can also be configured to he=
alth check backend services with automatic failover to healthy resources. <=
/span> <br> <br> <span style=3D"font-family:'Amazon Ember'; font-size:9pt; =
font-weight:bold">AWS WAF - Web Application Firewall</span> <span style=3D"=
font-family:'Amazon Ember'; font-size:9pt"> will be used to mitigate web ap=
plication attacks at Layer 7. It allows you to create security rules which =
will block traffic and can be configured to use Managed Rules provided by A=
WS or rules provided by 3rd Party WAF providers in the AWS Marketplace. Man=
aged Rules allow customers to configure WAF quickly and easily to meet thre=
ats like the OWASP Top 10 and are frequently updated. Customers can also cr=
eate their own rules and WAF can be configured by API to automatically resp=
ond to dynamic threats, for example blocking a specific IP which has been i=
dentified as malicious by other services such as Amazon GuardDuty or if tra=
ffic exceeds a specific rate threshold. </span> <br> <br> <span style=3D"fo=
nt-family:'Amazon Ember'; font-size:9pt; font-weight:bold">AWS Firewall Man=
ager</span> <span style=3D"font-family:'Amazon Ember'; font-size:9pt"> will=
 be used in conjunction with AWS Organizations to centrally manage the depl=
oyment of AWS WAF across accounts and applications. This provides consisten=
cy across all the accounts and applications and allow BOI to enforce mandat=
ory security polices. AWS Firewall Manager also supports the management of =
VPC Security Groups which act as stateful firewalls to VPC hosted resources=
 like EC2 and RDS. It will provide real time notification of misconfigured =
rules and corrective action can be taken within the Firewall Manager consol=
e as well as via automation.</span> <br> <span style=3D"font-family:'Amazon=
 Ember'; font-size:9pt">&nbsp;</span> </p>=20
